						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Vīrapratāpa Dēvarāya Year: Śaka 1353, <hi rend="italic">virōdhikiṟi, Makara</hi>, śu. Full Moon, Thursday <hi rend="italic">Pūśam</hi>, lunar eclipse = January 17, 1432 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records a gift of a village Bālavārai at Padiēripaṟṟu, near Rājagambhīran (division), to the god Tirumūlanayiṉār in Maṅgala-nāḍu, on the auspicious occasion of lunar eclipse for burning a lamp and providing food offering onetime <hi rend="italic">(oru-sandhi)</hi> by Aṇṇāmaḷaināthar, son of Nārasiṅgadēvar an official of Malaipaṟṟu. It is recorded that this grant was made for the victory and glory of the king, Dēvarāya mahārāya.</p>						

						</summary>
